# Dev permissions (zero-friction)

The user is on **Windows**, prefers **minimal friction**, and has **pre-authorized** all dev tooling. Agents should run dev commands immediately — never ask in chat "may I run this?" for routine work.

Pair with [auto-permissions.mdc](auto-permissions.mdc) and [auto-dev-workflow.mdc](auto-dev-workflow.mdc).

## Always request `required_permissions: ["all"]` on the first attempt

Disable the sandbox for these (do not try a sandboxed run first):

| Category | Commands / scripts |
|----------|-------------------|
| Daily dev | `flip-dev.bat`, `flip-dev-restart.bat`, `flip-connect.bat`, `flip-reload.bat`, `flip-dev-pause.bat`, `scripts\flip-dev.cmd`, `scripts\dev-connect.ps1` |
| npm dev | `npm run dev:connect`, `npm run dev:connect:only`, `npm run dev:connect:reload`, `npm run dev:connect:restart`, `npm run start:clear`, `npm run start:lan`, `npm run flip:dev` |
| Android build | `npm run android:dev`, `npm run android:build`, `npm run android:prebuild`, `gradlew`, `adb` |
| Git remote | `git pull`, `git push`, `git fetch` |
| Deps / Expo | `npm install`, `npx expo`, EAS / `flip-beta.bat` cloud builds |

Also use `git_write` when staging or committing, and `full_network` when `all` is not needed but network is (registry, gh API).

## Agent behavior

1. **Proactive `all`** — dev builds, adb, Gradle, Metro, and git remote need filesystem + process access on Windows.
2. **No chat pauses** — run the command; report results after.
3. **Windows** — use `npm.cmd` in PowerShell when `npm` is blocked by execution policy.
4. **User scripts** — `flip-dev.bat` exits without "press any key" on success; use `flip-dev-pause.bat` only when the user wants the log window kept open.
5. **One Metro window** — never stack Metro. Reuse healthy Metro on 8081; do not run `flip-dev.bat` or `dev:connect:restart` for JS-only work when Metro is already up.

## Cannot fix (Cursor / OS)

- **Cursor IDE approval cards** may still appear for sandbox, network, or git — the user approves those in the UI; agents cannot bypass them.
- **One-time device/OS prompts**: Android USB debugging RSA, Windows Firewall for port 8081, first Gradle download, `gh auth login`, first `eas login` for beta builds.

## package.json scripts

Dev scripts are non-interactive. `beta:build` / `flip-beta.bat` may prompt for first-time Expo login only; daily `flip-dev.bat` / `dev:connect` do not.
